+## 211 Partner Pilot Drill
+
+Run this drill in staging before a service partner pilot or rehearsal:
+
+```bash
+pytest tests/test_wallet_interface_api.py tests/test_wallet_third_party_blackbox.py -q
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui run build
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui test -- tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts
+```
+
+Pilot pass criteria:
+
+1. The user adds a document through Uploads and a precise location through Proof
+   Center. Evidence shows wallet record IDs and encrypted storage status only.
+2. The user shares the document with the partner DID for a named purpose. The
+   grant receipt shows `record/analyze` and `redacted_derived_only`; it must not
+   imply plaintext decrypt unless that is the explicit pilot scope.
+3. The partner runs redacted analysis from Recipient access. Inspect the output
+   and browser/API logs for emails, phone numbers, SSNs, plaintext document
+   bodies, and other direct identifiers.
+4. The user creates a location-region proof. Inspect proof public inputs and UI
+   text for latitude, longitude, witness values, target coordinates, verifier
+   credentials, or raw location payloads.
+5. The user opts in to an approved analytics template and contributes only
+   approved derived/coarse fields. Confirm the template has a completed
+   governance packet, consent copy, nullifier policy, threshold, privacy budget,
+   retention mapping, and reviewer role evidence.
+6. The user revokes the partner grant. Re-run a partner analysis/export/proof
+   call that depended on the grant and confirm it fails. Then confirm
+   `/grant-receipts?status=revoked` includes the grant.
+7. The Audit screen and `GET /wallets/{wallet_id}/audit` show the full workflow:
+   `grant/create`, `record/analyze_redacted`, `proof/create`,
+   `analytics/consent_create`, `analytics/contribute`, and `grant/revoke`.
+
+Capture only wallet IDs, record IDs, grant IDs, proof IDs, aggregate result IDs,
+receipt hashes, storage status, audit event IDs, and validation command output.
+Do not archive plaintext documents, precise coordinates, proof witnesses,
+recipient private keys, API bearer tokens, verifier credentials, Kubernetes
+Secret payloads, or screenshots that expose those values.
+
+If any pilot step exposes precise coordinates or plaintext outside the wallet
+boundary, stop the rehearsal, revoke affected grants, rotate affected record
+keys, preserve the audit trail, and follow the Privacy Incident section below.
+
